# Rebuilding Design with `astro-darkness` Template

This plan outlines the complete overhaul of your existing website to migrate from the current light Tailwind-based design to the `astro-darkness` template, which features a modern dark aesthetic, glassmorphism UI, and interactive Three.js particle backgrounds.

## User Review Required

Please review the process below. Since `astro-darkness` uses traditional CSS and Astro component-scoped styling instead of Tailwind CSS, we will be replacing our current components while maintaining the data architecture we've built for your Services and Portfolio.

## 1. Goal

Completely transform the user interface to emulate the [astro-darkness template](https://github.com/kpab/astro-darkness) without losing the AS Creative content, customized data collections, or the newly corrected clients list.

## 2. Dependencies & Global Configuration

#### [NEW] Dependencies
- Install the `three` and `@types/three` packages via npm, which are required for the `ThreeBackground.astro` particle effects.

#### [MODIFY] Global Styles
- Overwrite `src/styles/global.css` with the developer dark theme CSS variables defined in the `astro-darkness` template. We will adapt the primary branding colors (Blue/Purple/Cyan) from the default template to fit AS Creative's brand if desired, but we will start with the default gorgeous Abyss Theme.

## 3. Component Migration

I have already downloaded the `astro-darkness` repository to our scratch directory. I will selectively copy the raw template files over:

#### [MODIFY] Overwriting base structures:
- Add `src/components/ThreeBackground.astro`
- Overwrite `src/layouts/Layout.astro` (using `BaseLayout.astro` logic from the template).
- Overwrite `src/components/Navigation.astro` (replacing the React navbar with the template's floating glassmorphism Astro navbar).
- Overwrite `src/components/Hero.astro` to match the template's bold typography and effects.
- Add `src/components/ProjectCard.astro` and `src/components/Card.astro` to use the template's standard card layouts.

## 4. Retaining & Integrating Content

We will preserve the data layer (`src/content/` and `src/content.config.ts`) and loop that data into the newly styled components.

#### [MODIFY] `src/pages/index.astro`
- Integrate `ThreeBackground`.
- Remap our Service Collections to `Card.astro`.
- Map our Portfolio items to the new `ProjectCard.astro`.

#### [MODIFY] `src/components/Clients.astro`
- Update the Clients section classes. Since the background will be dark (`#0F172A`), we need to change the client logo grids so they contrast perfectly with a dark background. (e.g., glassmorphism containers instead of solid white backgrounds).

#### [MODIFY] `src/pages/about.astro`, `src/pages/contact.astro`, and `/services/[slug].astro`
- Wrap all content in the dark theme layouts, apply glowing text or shimmer effects for headers, and utilize the template's `Space Grotesk` typography fonts where necessary.

## Verification Plan

### Automated / Manual Verification
1. Run `npm install` to grab `three`.
2. Execute `npm run dev` and visually inspect the server rendering.
3. Validate that the particle background animation functions perfectly on the home page.
4. Ensure all links point to the right data schemas and no 404s appear for dynamic content slugs.

Once you approve this plan, I will immediately begin migrating the component and CSS files over and wire them into the AS Creative content!
